title: 820-3476-a orange light not turning on
message:
Don't waste time checking for S4 voltage, if don't get SUS voltage before.
And of course, no reason to search for S3 at all.

Be sure to use original 60/85W Magsafe 2 charger.
Check PM_DSW_PWRGD, PCH_DSWVRMEN, PM_BATLOW_L and all PCH's RTC signals.

title: 820-3476-a orange light not turning on
message:
Yes, im using an 85W oem charger.

PM_DSW_PWRGD: 1.3v

PCH_DSWVRMEN: 0.429v

PM_BATLOW_L: 3.3v

PPVRTC_G3H: 0.429 v

PCH_CLK32K_RTCX1: 0.42v

PPVOUT_S0_PCH_DCPRTC: 0v

PCH_SRTCRST_L: 0.46v

RTC_RESET_L: 0.425v

title: 820-3476-a orange light not turning on
message: Diode mode to ground at pin 1 of U1900?

title: 820-3476-a orange light not turning on
message:
Inspect all filter caps connected there; start with C1910.
If all good, replace U1900.

title: 820-3476-a orange light not turning on
message: C0892 was bad, replaced and computer works great now. Thanks a lot.
